# Google Maps Integration for Dashboard Booking Order Tracking

Integrate Google Maps API into the admin dashboard so that booking orders are detected by location and displayed as interactive markers on a real map.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> You will need a **Google Maps API key** with the following APIs enabled:
> - Maps JavaScript API
> - Geocoding API
>
> Please provide your API key so I can add it to [.env.local](file:///d:/car%20rental%20landing%20page/frontend/.env.local) as `NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY`.

> [!NOTE]
> **Approach: Client-Side Geocoding** — When the booking form is submitted, we'll use the Google Geocoding API to convert the `pickup_location` text into lat/lng coordinates and store them in Supabase. For existing bookings without coordinates, the dashboard map will geocode them on-the-fly and cache the results.

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Dependencies & Environment

#### [MODIFY] [package.json](file:///d:/car%20rental%20landing%20page/frontend/package.json)
- Install `@react-google-maps/api` — the standard React wrapper for Google Maps JS API

#### [MODIFY] [.env.local](file:///d:/car%20rental%20landing%20page/frontend/.env.local)
- Add `NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=<user-provided-key>`

---

### 2. Database Schema

#### [MODIFY] [schema.sql](file:///d:/car%20rental%20landing%20page/backend/schema.sql)
- Add `booking_lat DOUBLE PRECISION` and `booking_lng DOUBLE PRECISION` columns to the `bookings` table
- These store geocoded coordinates from the pickup location

---

### 3. Redux Store — Booking Slice

#### [MODIFY] [bookingSlice.ts](file:///d:/car%20rental%20landing%20page/frontend/src/store/slices/bookingSlice.ts)
- Add `booking_lat` and `booking_lng` to the [Booking](file:///d:/car%20rental%20landing%20page/frontend/src/store/slices/bookingSlice.ts#4-20) interface
- Update `createBooking` thunk to geocode the `pickup_location` before inserting into Supabase
- Update `fetchBookings` to include `booking_lat` and `booking_lng` from the database
- Add a `geocodeLocation` utility function that calls the Google Geocoding API

---

### 4. Dashboard Map Component

#### [MODIFY] [MapTracking.tsx](file:///d:/car%20rental%20landing%20page/frontend/src/components/dashboard/MapTracking.tsx)
Complete rewrite — replace static placeholder with interactive Google Map:

- **Google Map rendering** via `@react-google-maps/api` (`GoogleMap`, `LoadScript`)
- **Booking markers**: Read bookings from Redux store, place `Marker` on map for each booking with coordinates
- **On-the-fly geocoding**: For existing bookings without lat/lng, geocode `pickup_location` client-side and display
- **Info windows**: Click a marker to see a popup with booking details (car name, guest name, phone, dates, status)
- **Status color-coding**: Markers colored by status (🟡 pending, 🟢 confirmed, 🔵 completed, ⚫ cancelled)
- **Search bar**: Filter visible markers by guest name, car name, or location text
- **Auto-fit bounds**: Map auto-zooms to fit all visible markers

---

### 5. Booking Form — Geocode on Submit

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx (booking)](file:///d:/car%20rental%20landing%20page/frontend/src/app/booking/page.tsx)
- Update `createBooking` dispatch call to also pass geocoded lat/lng from the pickup location

---

## Verification Plan

### Browser Testing (QA)
1. **Navigate to dashboard** at `http://localhost:3000/dashboard`
   - Verify the Google Map renders instead of the static placeholder image
   - Verify the map is interactive (pan, zoom)

2. **Check booking markers**
   - Verify existing bookings appear as colored markers on the map
   - Verify markers are color-coded by status (pending=yellow, confirmed=green, etc.)

3. **Click a marker**
   - Verify an info window opens showing car name, guest name, phone, dates, and status

4. **Search functionality**
   - Type a guest name or car name in the search bar
   - Verify markers filter to show only matching bookings

5. **Create a new booking** via the booking page
   - Verify the new booking appears as a marker on the dashboard map after refresh

6. **Console errors**
   - Check browser console for any JavaScript errors or Google Maps API warnings
